  "text": "In countries like Israel, paid donors are forbidden, and so the only source of eggs is infertile patients undergoing assisted reproductive treatment cycles [CITATION_1] . Obviously, only a few oocytes are donated; thus an accurate ICSI technique is imperative for success in these cases. Recently [CITATION_2] reported on their experience with ICSI in donated eggs. However, this is a small group of only 15 cycles and therefore the conclusions are limited.",
